  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 4 for SLE 15 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 5.3.18-59_16 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2022-1048: Fixed a race Condition in snd_pcm_hw_free leading to use-after-free due to the AB/BA lock with buffer_mutex and mmap_lock (bsc#1197597).\n- CVE-2022-30594: Fixed restriction bypass on setting the PT_SUSPEND_SECCOMP flag (bnc#1199602).\n- Add missing module_mutex lock to module notifier for previous live patches (bsc#1199834).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
